<Author>simonsimonsimon
<Content>Great hotel Stayed here on a working trip here and it was a fabulous hotel.The hotel is very clean and the rooms are modern. There is what looked like an old balcony (it is still there) but the door handle is not on there any more. so dont expect a balcony. Was not bothered about the view as we did not spend much time in the room. I was in a single, but had a large double and when we checked in, we ventured out, and came back and we had a bottle of wine and a fruit bowl left in our room and compliments of the manager (possibly to do with our job role)The location is brilliant. I must warn you though, do not go by google maps as it is in the complete wrong direction. The hotel is inbetween Diagonal and Verdaguar metro stops, not by the Hospital. Which makes it a better location that it is on google maps!The breakfast was basic but nice and the staff were very friendly. Checked in and out with ease.Overall a very pleseant stay at the hotel! 
