<Author>VeryPickyLondon_UK
<Content>Your Stuff May Just Disappear!!!! - Room: nice clean and renovated. Very big. We had a separate TV room and a big balcony!! However, both TVs in room didn't work!!! We didn't mind since we were tired at night anyway.- Breakfast: Lots of choices but greasy- No nice communal area. You basically come in and go to your room- Location: close to Passeig de Gracia - Far from Rambla or port. Location felt very safe but if you want to walk to places, this is going to be a long walk. - Service: Cleaning lady moves your stuff!!!! I travel 50% of my work time and never use closet and keep my stuff in bag. The cleaning lady put my clothes in the closet and closed the closet door. We didn't check it when leaving. I called and they charged me 45 Euro to send me back my stuff. I agreed since my expensive brand belt was left there. Guess what? My cheap old clothes arrived AND THE BELT DISAPPEARED!!!!! I called and emailed and they just ignored me. Somebody there liked my belt and just decided to keep it AND charge me 45 for sending back my dirty t-shirts!!!!!!! Now I call this really really really bad service. Very unprofessional and not acceptable for a 3 or 4 star hotel. I don't feel safe in this hotel and am lucky that only my belt is disappeared, since if they take a belt they may take whatever precious!!! I wouldn't go back or if I were you, I wouldn't take any precious items around!!! Also the concierge is not helpful at all. While staying there we asked couple questions and they just acted as if we are annoying. 
