<Content>Really nice hotel Me and my husband went to the Catalonia Corsega for a city break earlier this month. The hotel was very clean and very quiet. It is in an excellent position to visit the Sagrada Familiar by foot. The only thing I would warn people about is the road the hotel is situated on - Calle de Corsega is a long road that runs across the city with the Passage de Gracia running through the middle, we took the bus from the airport and got off in the centre. It isnt clear on the directions and we turned the wrong way down the road, altogether it took us 2 hours to find the hotel. The breakfast was really good with a wide choice. We found all the staff to be pleasant and would definately go back. 
