<Content>Good Hotel, Good Location... Hotel was as good as the previous reviews i had read. My partner  i stayed for 4 nights and were given the 8th floor (top of the house!). The bonus was that we got a roof terrace - only 1 of 2 at the hotel - so ask for room 802 or 803!! Room, although on the small side, was clean. Everything you would need. Ideal location from which to explore this wonderful city. Just minutes from Passaig De Gracia which leads down to La Ramblas - about 20-25mins walk. Plenty of designer shops intermingled with tapas bars, restaurants and coffee/ice cream houses. Take the Tourist bus and see the whole city - north and south for just 鈧?9. Do the rest on foot and savour the hustle and bustle of this city. Not the most polite of people - this part of Spain is renowned for that - but it didn't ruin anything for us - just added to the experience! 
