<Content>Great hotel I stayed here with a friend (i.e. we鈥檙e two 33 yr old laydeeeez). Breakfast was very good (although the tea was a little weak and not hot how us British like it!).It's about 20 mins walk to Las Ramblas (whilst walking you pass many designer shops, coffee shops and bars).The sight-seeing bus pick-up point is about 5-10 min walk (in the same direction to Las Ramblas),where you can pick up buses which tour either north or south of the city.Although the hotel is on the outskirts of the hustle  bustle, it's nice and quiet (so you can sleep in peacefully). We didn't hear any of our neighbours.The road outside seemed to get busy with traffic, but there鈥檚 double-glazing, so not a problem, but then we were on the 6th floor.There are black-out curtains. The safe is 4 Euros/per day (40 Euros deposit). The tv could be better, the only English speaking channel was CNN (there are pay per view films).Lots of mirrors throughout which is great when you鈥檙e getting ready.The room isn鈥檛 especially luxurious, quite basic looking really, but it鈥檚 clean and comfortable.Bathroom is clean, with a bath  good shower. There鈥檚 a fridge, but no tea  coffee making facilities.Most people at reception spoke good English, but you can get by without too much of a problem. I would stay at this hotel again. 
