<Author>PeteUK
<Content>Fantastic Stay Our stay in the hotel was fantastic and could not be faulted. The staff were extremely friendly and helped wherever possible. Although the hotel was quite full, our room was quiet and we managed to have a lay in or two after some late nights without that noise you usually get in busy hotels. This is mainly due to the good layout of the rooms. The A/C in the room was great. It is very quite and works extremely well, not like some of the noisy malfunctioning ones you get in some hotels! It would have been nice to have a pool, but we were never really there so much during the day, so we would not have used it anyway. It is close to Diagonal Metro stop. We took the train from the airport to the hotel without a problem (a few stairs to deal with on the Metro though). The location of the hotel is also in a very good and in a safe part of town with lots of shops and places to eat down PG de Gracia and further up Av Diagonal. A lot of the Gaudi Modernist buildings are also nearby. Although not close to the Rabalas, I would rather stay in this location where it is safer and quieter. Breakfast at the hotel was awesome and saw us through the day until a late afternoon snack. 10/10! I would definitely recommend this hotel and go back there should I visit Barcelona again. 
