<Author>Continent_Jumper
<Content>Great city, great hotel Booked as part of a package so we were a little apprehensive, especially reading some of the reviews here. In fact the hotel was great and comparable with any four star hotels we've stayed in.Room was a good size, bathroom very nice, marble walls and nice touches like a bidet and complimentary shaving kit. The downsides were the TV channels, only CNN News was in English and we had a rear-facing room, with a view of an adjacent apartment block.We booked on a bb basis, breakfast was very good, fresh pastries and cereal, good choice and friendly staff.The hotel has the advantage of being in a quiet neighbourhood with the proximity to all the main attractions. Although it's a good 30-40 minutes walk to La Rambla from the hotel, the Metro station is near (Diagonal) and really easy to use. To walk to La Rambla you pass through Passeig de Gracia and Place de la Catalunya, which are very pleasant for shopping and also contains Gaudi's La Pedrera and Casa Battlo. La Sagrada Familia is only about 5 blocks away.The hotel is on Corcega, which was right in the middle of the August festival with streets bedecked in colour and live performances, which topped off a great stay. Would recommend this hotel to anyone. 
