<Content>Would stay here again Four of us visited Barcelona from 7/11/04-10/11/04 and stayed at this hotel. I was a bit apprehensive after reading some of the reviews, but I cannot disagree strongly enough. The hotel was spotless, including the rooms, and even though we only stayed 3 nights, the sheets were changed on the third. The breakfast was wonderful, buffet and no limit to amount. The evening meals were a bit limited (for my taste, and the only reason I didn't give 5 stars) but excellent value, 12.62 euros for 3 courses incl wine, water and coffee. The chocolate ice cream is to die for! The staff were pleasant and helpful and the hotel is well situated. We were 6 floors up above the front street which was quite busy, but the rooms are triple glazed and noise wasn't a problem, even though I am a light sleeper. When I return this will definitely be my first choice. 
