<Content>So, so Just returned form 5 nights at this hotel and while it was merely okay, it somewhat lacked in friendliness and cleanliness.The front of house staff were absolutely fine and helpful, however, the restuarant staff were another matter. Breakfast was served between 7.30 and 10.30am, however, if you arrived at 10.15am you would be abruptly told you had one minute to get your breakfast from the buffet, they also started to remove the breakfast at 10.25am. There was not one smile or friendly face at breakfast. Dinner was pretty much the same, however, the food was value for money. The bedroom and bathroom were merely skimmed over each day, with horrendous dust balls under the bed and in the corners and badly smeared taps etc. in the bathroom. Our sheets were not changed once.While the hotel was okay, it is DEFINITELY NOT a 4 star hotel (although the blue plaque outside on the wall does have 4 stars).In addition, the hotel was extremely noisy with people shouting on the stairwells, doors slamming very loudly and football being played after midnight on the second floor (we were on the 6th!!!). We found it was very well located, just off Pag. de Gracia with Catalunya Sq and La Rambla a 20 min walk down Pag. de Gracia (2 metro stops). Also Sagrada Famialia 10 mins walk away, La Pedrera and Casa Batllo 5 mins walk down Passeo de Gracia.If you want more information please contact me. 
