<Content>Great hotel, friendly staff, clean rooms This hotel was lovely, the reception staff were more than helpful, the rooms were very clean and a really good size. The marble bathroom was also very clean and the shower was fantastic!The location was ok, it is a little far out from the main streets, and it is advised that you learn your way around before you get there, or at least carry a map at all times! We stayed for a long weekend, and had learned the route back to the hotel from the main street by the time we were leaving! It is however only about 15-20mins walk to Las Ramblas which is handy.We had breakfast every morning and there was a good selection of food, with a cooked section, cereals, fruit, croissants, toast and a wide range of toppings!Overall it was a lovely hotel to stay in, especially when we didn't really spend much time in the hotel. It was a good base, and was very quiet so we could sleep well and rest our tired legs from all the sightseeing! 
