<Content>Excellent Location Visited this hotel in July 2003 and was very very pleased with this 3* Plus hotel which is situated in the heart of everything. Minutes walk to Catalunya Square, La Ramblas (where all the shops and restaurants are), the Metro (very cheap 1.05 Euro's for a single trip anywhere, safe, clean). If you want to walk everywhere, it is possible but where suitable footwear...we walked to most places...it was fun, but tiring towards the end of the day. The Port is about 10-15 minute walk...good nightlife there.Situated on a busy pedestrianised street (which is brilliant for shopping) but peaceful inside. Rooms were a good size for two, A/C, amazingly clean, bathrooms all marble. Good choise of breakfast. Staff were very freindly and helpful. Alberto at reception was especially good and helped us find places to visit.I would definately recommend it. Please email me if you want further information. A littel tip...learn some Spanish before you go there....communication is a problem. 
